3 Section 7. Section 27-30-204, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "27-30-204. Abatement of public nuisance by public body government entity or officer or
5 injured party. A public nuisance may be abated by any public body a government entity or officer authorized
6 by law. A person may abate a public nuisance that is specially injurious to that person by removing or, if
7 necessary, destroying the thing that constitutes the nuisance, as long as doing so would not constitute without
8 committing a breach of the peace or cause doing unnecessary injury. Nothing in this section alters the remedies
9 to a government entity or private person in a public nuisance cause of action."
